@node index
@section @code{index}---search for character in string
@findex index
@strong{Synopsis}
@example
#include <strings.h>
char * index(const char *@var{string}, int @var{c});

@end example
@strong{Description}@*
This function finds the first occurence of @var{c} (converted to
a char) in the string pointed to by @var{string} (including the
terminating null character).

This function is identical to @code{strchr}.

@*
@strong{Returns}@*
Returns a pointer to the located character, or a null pointer
if @var{c} does not occur in @var{string}.

@*
@strong{Portability}@*
@code{index} requires no supporting OS subroutines.

@*
